06:17.605 --> 06:18.445
Trust me.

06:21.045 --> 06:21.885
It's Pat.

06:22.285 --> 06:23.165
Postman Pat?

06:23.245 --> 06:24.085
Yeah.

06:25.245 --> 06:26.525
Put it through the door.

06:36.005 --> 06:37.285
That was easy, wasn't it?

06:37.445 --> 06:39.245
-You could've done that.
-No, I couldn't.

06:39.325 --> 06:40.565
-Why not?
-I'm not a postman.

06:42.245 --> 06:43.085
Go on.

06:52.725 --> 06:53.565
Hi, George.

06:54.405 --> 06:55.325
Hi.

06:55.725 --> 06:56.685
Who's that?

06:56.925 --> 06:57.805
He's my uncle.

06:58.685 --> 06:59.805
[boy] Pedo!

07:00.205 --> 07:02.005
-What?
-Pedo!

07:03.525 --> 07:04.685
I'm not a pedo.

07:04.765 --> 07:07.045
And if I was, you'd be safe,
you tubby little ginger cunt.

07:07.125 --> 07:08.125
[mouthing]

07:11.605 --> 07:12.565
Welcome.

07:12.725 --> 07:13.725
Great to have you.

07:13.805 --> 07:16.325
I remember my first day,
and it is exciting, isn't it?

07:16.405 --> 07:18.165
-Yeah.
-Yeah. Great place to work, this.

07:18.245 --> 07:21.285
Very dynamic, lots of people
in and out all the time.

07:21.365 --> 07:23.365
Really excellent bunch of people.

07:24.245 --> 07:25.165
Hard working.

07:25.885 --> 07:28.765
It's very rewarding as well.
You get to go out into the community.

07:29.165 --> 07:32.605
And that can be anything
from local stories, you know,

07:33.365 --> 07:35.765
um... entertainment, finance.

07:36.845 --> 07:37.885
So, yeah.

07:38.085 --> 07:39.445
Kath does the advertising.

07:39.765 --> 07:42.525
Be nice to her, and she might take you
to the opening of a new restaurant,

07:42.605 --> 07:44.285
give you a free meal. [laughs]

07:44.365 --> 07:46.245
Lenny does all the photography,

07:46.325 --> 07:47.725
so if you're interested in that...

07:47.805 --> 07:49.925
Everyone chips in on everything, really.

07:50.005 --> 07:52.365
So what kind of thing are you
interested in, would you say?

07:52.445 --> 07:53.965
Um, writing features.

07:54.045 --> 07:55.085
Perfect. That's great.

07:55.165 --> 07:56.525
You'll definitely do that here.

07:57.045 --> 07:59.045
Lots of features. Sky's the limit.

07:59.525 --> 08:00.365
Um...

08:01.005 --> 08:02.605
Tony's the head of features.

08:02.725 --> 08:03.605
He's not here.

08:04.325 --> 08:05.605
He's a very good writer.

08:05.685 --> 08:08.325
Very smart, very experienced,
good guy. Um...

08:10.605 --> 08:12.885
He's not himself at the minute,
to be honest.

08:13.245 --> 08:14.965
He's had a bit of bad news. Um...

08:15.925 --> 08:18.085
His, er... Tony's my brother-in-law.

08:18.485 --> 08:21.245
Um, he was married to my sister, Lisa,

08:22.045 --> 08:22.965
who died.

08:24.685 --> 08:25.565
Cancer.

08:27.405 --> 08:29.525
-[stuttering] Sorry.
-Yeah.

08:30.005 --> 08:32.005
And he was obviously devastated.

08:33.005 --> 08:34.245
Er, suicidal.

08:35.765 --> 08:36.605
Right.

08:37.925 --> 08:39.805
I should warn you, he might...

08:39.965 --> 08:41.965
say a few things that are a bit...

08:42.325 --> 08:43.245
er...

08:43.485 --> 08:44.325
brutal...

08:45.045 --> 08:48.205
at times, so, you know,
don't take it personally.

08:48.965 --> 08:51.205
I mean, you will be
working closely with him.

08:52.565 --> 08:53.405
Anyway, er...

08:53.685 --> 08:55.165
-have fun.
-[laughs nervously]

08:56.845 --> 08:57.685
Thanks.

08:58.925 --> 08:59.805
So, how are you?

09:01.005 --> 09:01.925
Same.

09:02.725 --> 09:03.845
Bad then?

09:04.125 --> 09:06.165
I've honestly nothing
to compare it to anymore.

09:06.605 --> 09:08.685
But I guess a good day

09:08.765 --> 09:10.565
is when I don't go around

09:10.645 --> 09:12.845
wanting to shoot random strangers
in the face

09:12.925 --> 09:14.525
and then turn the gun on myself.

09:15.525 --> 09:16.445
[tuts]

09:18.725 --> 09:19.885
[laughs under breath]

09:21.045 --> 09:22.445
One of my clients

09:22.965 --> 09:25.565
fantasizes about killing his ex-wife...

09:26.525 --> 09:28.045
[whispering] ...when he's masturbating.

09:28.845 --> 09:31.205
-Why are you telling me that?
-I didn't say his name.

09:31.325 --> 09:32.285
No, I know, but...

09:32.805 --> 09:33.765
how does that help me?

09:33.845 --> 09:34.925
[sighs deeply]

09:35.445 --> 09:36.565
I dunno.

09:37.485 --> 09:40.245
I guess to let you know
you're not the only one.

09:41.125 --> 09:41.965
Only what?

09:42.045 --> 09:43.845
Well, the only mental case out there.

09:44.565 --> 09:45.845
I mean, you know...

09:47.245 --> 09:49.405
the only guy with mental problems.

09:49.925 --> 09:51.525
-I've got problems.
-Go on.

09:51.605 --> 09:53.285
[scoffs] God, man, where do I start?

09:53.925 --> 09:56.045
Maybe start with me, as I'm paying, but...

10:00.005 --> 10:01.365
-Morning.
-Morning.

10:01.925 --> 10:04.645
Terrible, isn't it? Scarred for life.

10:05.445 --> 10:06.965
Hardly scarred for life.

10:07.205 --> 10:08.245
She's 93.

10:08.805 --> 10:11.525
If she lives to 100, she's only been
scarred for seven percent of her life.

10:21.165 --> 10:22.165
[woman] You're late.

10:22.725 --> 10:23.605
You're boring.

10:23.925 --> 10:24.925
You're joking, aren't you?

10:25.005 --> 10:26.685
I wasn't, but go on. What have you got?

10:26.925 --> 10:28.245
It's distribution day.

10:28.325 --> 10:31.325
No, I mean, why would you think
I was joking about you being boring?

10:31.405 --> 10:33.925
Have you got a... counterargument or...

10:35.485 --> 10:38.045
-Why do you let him get away with this?
-I don't. [stuttering]

10:38.125 --> 10:39.685
Tony, come on. What's going on?

10:40.125 --> 10:42.365
Er, we're putting out
a free local newspaper

10:42.445 --> 10:45.245
-that no one cares about.
-No, that's... That's not true.

10:45.325 --> 10:47.085
And that's not what...
Can you come in my office?

10:47.445 --> 10:48.285
[Tony] Sure.

10:48.365 --> 10:51.485
A lot of people rely on our paper.
Not everyone's on Twitter, are they?

10:52.165 --> 10:53.445
Back to work, everyone.

10:55.965 --> 10:57.005
What do you want me to say?

10:57.085 --> 11:00.445
That I'm sorry, and I'll buck my ideas up?
'Cause I won't. 'Cause there's no point.

11:01.125 --> 11:03.205
Look, Tony, I know that you've had issues,

11:03.285 --> 11:05.485
-okay, since you lost Lisa.
-Do you reckon...

11:05.565 --> 11:07.165
my wife dying affected me a bit?

11:07.245 --> 11:10.045
Of course, and, you know, I get that.
I even told Sandy about it.

11:10.285 --> 11:11.365
Who's Sandy?

11:11.565 --> 11:14.325
The new girl. I didn't want her thinking
this place was a madhouse.

11:14.725 --> 11:16.285
I had to say something.

11:16.925 --> 11:19.485
Look, I just need a bit of professionalism
around here, okay, Tony.

11:19.565 --> 11:20.485
-Please?
-No.

11:20.565 --> 11:22.125
I shouldn't have to explain this to you.

11:22.205 --> 11:24.045
You can't just go around
being rude to people.

11:24.125 --> 11:24.965
You can, though.

11:25.365 --> 11:26.605
That's the beauty of it.

11:27.045 --> 11:29.885
There's no advantage
to being nice and thoughtful

11:29.965 --> 11:32.005
and caring and having integrity.

11:32.085 --> 11:33.925
It's a <i>disadvantage,</i> if anything.

11:34.005 --> 11:36.645
Let's see. If you carry on like this,
I might have to let you go.

11:36.725 --> 11:37.605
No, you won't.

11:38.085 --> 11:40.645
You won't, that's what I'm saying,
'cause you're a nice bloke.

11:40.725 --> 11:44.045
So I'll take advantage of you,
like everyone else does here.

11:44.125 --> 11:45.805
-You'll warn me. I'll ignore it.
-What?

11:45.885 --> 11:47.725
You'll give me another warning.
I'll ignore it.

11:47.805 --> 11:49.445
I'll carry on doing what the fuck I want.

11:49.525 --> 11:51.885
Eventually, you'll give up, and I'll win.

11:52.445 --> 11:54.445
The girls here have discovered

11:54.525 --> 11:57.485
that you won't even question
"women's problems."

11:57.565 --> 11:59.405
Kath's had three periods this month.

11:59.485 --> 12:01.685
She likes Fridays off. You do nothing.

12:01.765 --> 12:04.165
She gets away with it
'cause she's an arsehole.

12:04.245 --> 12:06.685
So, I thought, right,
let's have a bit of that.

12:06.765 --> 12:07.845
Why would you wanna do that?

12:07.925 --> 12:10.205
Why wouldn't you just rather
get better and be happy?

12:10.285 --> 12:12.365
There's only one thing
that'd make me better and happy,

12:12.445 --> 12:14.965
and that's Lisa being around,
and that can't happen.

12:15.045 --> 12:17.805
So that's why I nearly killed myself
straight away.

12:17.885 --> 12:20.485
Right, okay, but you didn't
kill yourself, did you?

12:20.845 --> 12:23.685
So, clearly, you know,
something made you stop.

12:23.765 --> 12:25.125
The look on the dog's face.

12:25.845 --> 12:28.085
She was hungry,
so I thought I'd better feed her.

12:28.405 --> 12:29.845
It gave me time to think,

12:29.925 --> 12:31.165
"I should be dead now."

12:31.245 --> 12:32.165
I didn't care.

12:32.325 --> 12:33.685
So, everything's a bonus.

12:34.685 --> 12:36.205
If I become an arsehole,

12:36.285 --> 12:39.005
and I do and say what the fuck I want

12:39.085 --> 12:40.445
for as long as I want,

12:40.525 --> 12:42.045
and then when it all gets too much,

12:42.125 --> 12:43.445
I can always kill myself.

12:43.805 --> 12:44.965
It's like a superpower.

12:45.205 --> 12:47.605
That's the worst superhero
I've ever heard of.

12:48.405 --> 12:49.685
That's the way it is now.

12:49.765 --> 12:50.845
[Braden] So what? So...

12:50.925 --> 12:51.805
[sighs]

12:52.245 --> 12:55.845
My job now is to make you happy
<i>before</i> you kill yourself?

12:55.925 --> 12:58.605
That's like a constant ticking clock
for me now, is it?

12:58.685 --> 12:59.725
If you like.

12:59.805 --> 13:01.085
Well, I don't like.

13:01.165 --> 13:03.205
Anyway, that's the way it is.

13:03.645 --> 13:05.565
[Braden] Okay, well,
I'm glad we had this chat.

13:05.645 --> 13:07.085
[Tony] Yeah, very constructive.

13:08.725 --> 13:09.845
All right, um...

13:10.645 --> 13:12.645
So this is... This is Sandy.

13:12.725 --> 13:16.165
She's just started today.
It's her first day, um, so, Tony,

13:16.245 --> 13:18.125
she's gonna be working under you.
If you could...

13:18.205 --> 13:20.085
show her the ropes, tell her what's what.

13:21.645 --> 13:23.325
Here's what's what. Um...

13:23.725 --> 13:25.165
humanity is a plague.

13:25.405 --> 13:29.165
We're a disgusting, narcissistic,
selfish parasite,

13:29.445 --> 13:31.525
and the world would be
a better place without us.

13:31.605 --> 13:33.805
It should be everyone's moral duty
to kill themselves.

13:33.885 --> 13:36.445
I could do it now.
Quite happily just go upstairs,

13:36.685 --> 13:37.765
jump off the roof,

13:37.845 --> 13:40.325
and make sure I landed
on some cunt from Accounts.

13:41.005 --> 13:43.965
That the sort of thing... you meant?

13:44.685 --> 13:45.685
No.

13:46.605 --> 13:47.965
Just, um... ignore that.

13:48.045 --> 13:50.765
Um, Lenny, can you show Sandy the ropes?

13:50.845 --> 13:51.845
Sure thing.

13:51.925 --> 13:53.725
[Braden] Gotta get the papers out.
Thank you.

13:53.805 --> 13:56.045
-[Tony] You showing her the ropes?
-[Lenny] Big-time.

13:56.165 --> 13:57.405
Can I guess the bullet points?

13:59.125 --> 14:00.005
Get in.

14:00.685 --> 14:02.045
